node.text:
See you at Robson Square today - Repost from @oldgrowthvancity
•
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
On Friday May 21 Vancouver shows up to stand in solidarity with land defenders at Fairy Creek. We gather on the unceded territories of the xʷməθkʷəy̓əm (Musqueam), Sḵwx̱wú7mesh (Squamish), and səlilwətaɬ (Tsleil-Waututh) Nations.
⁠
We stand with Elder Bill Jones
We stand with Kati George-Jim⁠
We stand with Aya Clappis⁠
We stand with all front line defenders who have been holding it down for the past 9 months.⁠
⁠
We stand to end colonial violence and un-checked resource extraction within our last critical endangered ecosystems. ⁠
⁠
We stand against the RCMP's establishment of unlawful exclusion zones and against the tactics employed by the RCMP, BC NDP, and BC FORESTRY.⁠
⁠
We reject BC NDP, John Horgan's and BC Forestry's campaign of misinformation.⁠
⁠
FAIRY CREEK - CAYCUSE - WALBRAN ⁠
⁠
This is just the beginning.⁠
⁠
**Join us - May 21st - at the Courthouse - 2PM-6PM⁠**⁠
⁠

30 JAVAN SLOW LORISES HAVE BEEN RELEASED!

Rescued from the illegal pet trade, these beautiful, Critically Endangered primates can now finally be free!
Please support @international_animal_rescue - they do such brave and brilliant work. And please never repost videos of ‘cute’ slow lorises being ‘tickled’. The Tickling is Torture campaign has done a lot to stop lorises being captured and tortured. Let’s keep wildlife wild and never encourage the illegal pet trade. 🙏🏽 

The release operation in Mt Halimun Salak National Park (TNGHS) was carried out by the Centre for Natural Resources Conservation (BBKSDA)  and IAR Indonesia.

Most of the lorises had been surrendered by members of the community to various sections of the BKSDA in the West Java region, and had then been cared for at the IAR Indonesia rescue centre. After undergoing medical examinations (which included a COVID-19 test) the lorises were then entered into a period of quarantine as a precautionary measure.

To ensure the lorises have the best chance of survival, the team then began the two-week process of habituating the lorises to their new environment. This process includes behavioural monitoring to ensure their natural instincts were strong enough for survival in the rainforest. After no abnormalities were shown, the team deemed the lorises ready for a full release into the national park!

TNGHS was chosen as the release location based on a habitat suitability assessment that had been carried out by a team from the TNGHS Office and IAR Indonesia. The release area has an ecosystem considered suitable as a place for the preservation and protection of slow lorises in terms of area security, availability of food and shade, habitat carrying capacity and the level of predator threats. The hope is that with this release, the slow lorises can reproduce and THRIVE!

Thank you to everyone that supports our lifesaving work. Without YOU, these lorises would have never stood a chance of survival.

Repost from @kenwukenwu
‘Last week I was fortunate to bring Nathalie Boltt @natboltt and her wonderful family, Phil her husband and Jupiter her son, on a tour of the amazing old-growth forests near Port Renfrew in Pacheedaht territory.

 Nathalie, who plays the evil villain Penelope Blossom in the hit series "Riverdale", has 2 million followers and has been a relentless champion for many years to protect old-growth forests in BC, and has worked to engage other celebrities in her circles to speak up.

 More photos and vids to come! 

Speak up to ensure the critical solutions to protect old-growth forests in BC at the link in my profile.’ … It was an absolute dream going on this adventure with Ken - and at a time of the worst heat wave in Canada that caused devastating wildfires, killing hundreds of people, thousands of animals, more forests…an untold toll of devastation for flora and fauna. Ask yourself - and your politicians- why are we allowing ancient forests, that absorb twice the amount of carbon compared to second growth forests, to be massacred for profit at this time of climate crisis? @johnhorgan4bc says he is doing ‘everything possible to stop wildfires’ - by enabling the logging of ancient trees for profit?! I urge you to speak up! Support @endangeredecosystemsalliance  as well as @fairycreekblockade  @thegreenparty_canada to halt old growth logging and negotiate  a new moratorium immediately. Now is the time. 🙏🏽- much love, Nat x

In honour of National Indigenous Day June 21st, these beautiful women and this update from Fairy Creek, who continue to need your support.  Repost from @rainforestflyingsquad
•
‘DAILY UPDATED 📌 (June 22, part 2) From @fairycreekblockade 

▪️A ceremony was held at HQ today to honour Indigenous People’s Day and the over 4000 murdered and missing Indigenous women, girls, and two-spirited whom RCMP couldn't care less about. This was not a memorial of an historic event. This is happening now. Our sisters are still being stolen. 

▪️To help dispel the thought that Horgan’s deferral is anything more than an attempt to score political points and disarm our supporters, we gathered evidence of active Old Growth Logging happening above Camper’s Creek in the Fairy Creek rainforest.

▪️RCMP denied our rights and risked disfiguring a forest defender today. If you’ve been following our updates, you’re familiar by now with the sleeping dragon - a tube cemented into the ground for a forest defender to lock their arm into. Today we employed a sleeping dragon made of metal and officers chose to use a grinder on the side of the pipe to access the chain around the defender’s wrist. Anyone who has operated a grinder knows how easy it is to burn oneself without heavy leather clothing, and how the disks of these tools can explode, mangling the hand of the operator and anyone nearby. Regardless, the RCMP’s safety precautions were limited  to pouring water down the tube to dampen sparks and cool the metal. The defender in this dragon was burned several times and hurt by police pulling on her tightly restrained arm.’ 
Why is the @ndpcanada  wasting our taxpayer money to destroy resources, threaten and endanger peaceful protesters and destroy ecosystems and indigenous lands? 

We need you. 
Come to camp.#nationalindigenouspeoplesday #fairycreek #stopoldgrowthlogging @markruffalo
